## 2. Set up your virtual machine

For this tutorial, you'll need to ensure that your virtual machine can access the Internet and has ports 22 (SSH) and 80 (HTTP) open to inbound traffic through the firewall. Port 80 is required because you'll set up a basic web server configuration later in this tutorial.

You'll also need two pieces of software on your virtual machine &ndash; the Chef Development Kit (Chef DK) and a good text editor.

### Verify network access

Although Chef can be run from behind the firewall, giving your virtual machine Internet access is the easiest way to install packages and perform other common tasks.

Ensure that your server can reach the Internet through your company's proxy server and firewall.

### Install the Chef Development Kit

Remember, for learning purposes, you'll start by managing a server directly. To do that, you'll install the Chef Development Kit on your virtual machine. The Chef DK provides tools that enable you to manage your servers remotely from your workstation. But it also provides tools that allow you to configure a machine directly.

Download and install the Chef DK on your virtual machine.

